dn.com/news/story/12539/5901492\">Lee Chun</a></span><span class=\"c2\"> (ææ·³)</span></li></ul></td><td class=\"list-set bubbles w-min-12 kmt ccp\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><ul class=\"c7 lst-kix_vwtxwqnjdenf-0 start\"><li class=\"c6 li-bullet-0 kmt\"><span class=\"c4\"><a class=\"c0\" href=\"https://www.cna.com.tw/news/aipl/202111020330.aspx\">Ling Tao</a></span><span class=\"c2\"> (å‡Œæ¿¤)</span></li><li class=\"c6 li-bullet-0 ccp\"><span class=\"c4\"><a class=\"c0\" href=\"http://www.taihainet.com/news/twnews/twdnsz/2021-10-29/2566212.html\">Taihai</a></span></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><p class=\"c14\"><span class=\"c8\">Based on the abovementioned 10 narratives, IORG has the following conclusions:</span></p><ul class=\"c7 lst-kix_qan38nhgta8r-0 start\"><li class=\"c5 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c8\">7 of the 8 information manipulation narratives are related to ractopamine pork, 1 is related to the protection of algal reefs and the Fourth Nuclear Power Plant. 2 government narratives also concern ractopamine pork.</span></li><li class=\"c5 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c8\">Based on the limited number of cases, ractopamine pork is more likely to be a topic of information manipulation among the 4 referendum topics. IORG argues two reasons: (1) Ractopamine pork directly concerns Taiwan-U.S. relations, the CCP has strong incentives to influence and direct Taiwanese public opinion towards U.S. skepticism and hostility. (2) Food safety is a sensitive topic to the people of Taiwan. By promoting health concerns on ractopamine pork, the CCP can amplify peopleâ€™s distrust towards the Taiwanese government.</span></li><li class=\"c5 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c8\">CCP participation can be found in all of the 10 narratives. Among the 10 narratives, 2 are initiated by the CCP: â€œTaiwanese pork products tested excessive ractopamine in Hongkongâ€ and â€œChinese state media quotes netizens to equate ractopamine pork with addictive drugs (â€œpoisonous substanceâ€)â€.</span></li><li class=\"c5 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c8\">â€œTaiwan purchased American ractopamine pork and weapons, therefore it should receive American vaccinesâ€, â€œBanning ractopamine pork is banning American porkâ€ and â€œTaiwan will be unable to join CPTPP if ractopamine pork import is bannedâ€ have the most number of Facebook posts, far outnumbering other 7 narratives.</span></li><li class=\"c5 li-bullet-0\"><span>CCP quotes netizens to spread these 2 narratives in criticizing the Taiwanese government: â€œThe ruling party imports ractopamine pork, selling out public healthâ€ and â€œChinese state media quotes netizens to equate ractopamine pork with addictive drugs (â€œpoisonous substanceâ€)â€. Similar situation has also been found in </span><span class=\"c18\"><a class=\"c0\" href=\"https://iorg.tw/da/10\">DA.10</a></span><span class=\"c8\">.</span></li><li class=\"c5 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c8\">Despite clarifications from Taiwanâ€™s Council of Agriculture (COA) and Mainland Affairs Council (MAC), the false narrative â€œTaiwanese pork products tested excessive ractopamine in Hongkongâ€, initiated by Chinese state media Wen Wei Po (æ–‡åŒ¯å ±) continues to spread among among LINE chat groups, and evolves into the narrative that â€œTaiwanâ€™s ractopamine pork products are on sale in Hongkong, so ractopamine pork is also being sold in Taiwanâ€. The updated narrative implies that â€œTaiwan actually has ractopamine porkâ€ and â€œthe government is lyingâ€.</span></li></ul><div class=\"separator\"></div><a id=\"t.ddc8da8f14956e0838fde572a21f3dff62665921\"></a><a id=\"t.3\"></a><div class=\"gdoc-photo-container\"><div class=\"images\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/AseVOmQmfZdK6U-A5FkOTdT37jPzUPIpGoL6nss2Q3fIu-m9A1wHXKW4-aQyey04xkN7SvT4M_5Qaefp9kDHlbUhgcnJbkt2VCNDxr5JpBT34TRjhQWkm3QxatwB7D8J7A\" title=\"\"></div></div><div class=\"separator\"></div><p class=\"c14\"><span>Full version of this Dokidoki Alert is available in Taiwanese Mandarin. Please visit </span><span class=\"c18\"><a class=\"c0\" href=\"https://iorg.tw/da/16\">https://iorg.tw/da/16</a></span><span class=\"c8\"> for more.</span></p><div class=\"separator\"></div><p class=\"c14\"><span class=\"c8\">Alsoâ€¦</span></p><ul class=\"c7 lst-kix_a52ds2ibcu8r-0 start\"><li class=\"c5 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c18\"><a class=\"c0\" href=\"https://iorg.tw/_en/open/research-method\">IORG Research Method</a></span></li><li class=\"c5 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c18\"><a class=\"c0\" href=\"https://iorg.tw/_en/china-watch\">IORG China Watch</a></span></li><li class=\"c5 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c18\"><a class=\"c0\" href=\"https://iorg.tw/_en/da\">IORG Dokidoki Alert</a></span></li></ul>",
